      "message": "Looking at the populateWorkQueueIfNeeded() code, it does indeed take two runs to reset locked handles AND get them into the queue:\n\n    if (moduleSyncWorkQueue.isEmpty()) {\n        populateWorkQueue();  // Nothing in first run, will be SECOND run\n        if (moduleSyncWorkQueue.isEmpty()) {\n            setPreviouslyLockedCmHandlesToAdvised(); // FIRST run\n            // locked are now advised, but not yet in the queue\n        }\n\nThe 2 times makes sense when you think this used to be two separate scheduled tasks.",
